# 439dcde8ba804ea5987c0bf80f1e1111
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSNetAcceptNamedProtocol.en.rst:36
msgid ""
":type:`TSNetAcceptNamedProtocol` registers the specified :arg:`protocol` "
"for all statically configured TLS ports.  When a client using the TLS "
"Next Protocol Negotiation extension negotiates the requested protocol, "
":type:`TrafficServer` will route the request to the given handler "
":arg:`contp`."
msgstr ""

# 742e8687900a48a78c06fd62ec82bbff
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSNetAcceptNamedProtocol.en.rst:43
msgid ""
"Be aware that the protocol is not registered on ports opened by other "
"plugins."
msgstr ""

# 290f919df4d2442987cee48098883e90
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSNetAcceptNamedProtocol.en.rst:46
msgid ""
"The event and data provided to the handler are the same as for "
":func:`TSNetAccept`.  If a connection is successfully accepted, the event"
" code will be :data:`TS_EVENT_NET_ACCEPT` and the event data will be a "
"valid :type:`TSVConn` bound to the accepted connection."
msgstr ""

# ac7c931cfeee4bf481d353ef9cd76cea
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSNetAcceptNamedProtocol.en.rst:53
msgid ""
"Neither :arg:`contp` nor :arg:`protocol` are copied. They must remain "
"valid for the lifetime of the plugin."
msgstr ""

# e1ac3121f5e348fb897095aae3f9f431
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSNetAcceptNamedProtocol.en.rst:56
msgid ""
":type:`TSNetAcceptNamedProtocol` fails if the requested protocol cannot "
"be registered on all of the configured TLS ports. If it fails, the "
"protocol will not be registered on any ports. There is no partial "
"failure."
msgstr ""

